							'description' => html_entity_decode('&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: medium; color: #0000ff;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Oxford Collocations Dictionary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;A completely new type of dictionary that will help students effectively study, write and speak natural-sounding English, also very helpful for the education of the IETLS, TOEFL tests.&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;The dictionary that helps students write and speak natural-sounding English, now in a new edition with CD-ROM. Which words usually go together? This dictionary shows you the common word combinations (collocations) that are essential for natural-sounding British and American English. Completely revised and extended, the new edition has over 250,000 collocations and over 75,000 examples.&lt;/p&gt;'), 
